The paper focuses on traffic management and forecasting using a virtual reality geographic information system, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). It also involves the use of real-time dynamic traffic information, which could be classified under computer engineering (cs.CE) or cybernetics (cs.CY). The analysis and monitoring of passenger flow could be considered as a form of data science, falling under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI). Finally, the use of GIS technology could also be classified under information technology (cs.IT).
